n werden: Einerseits formt Stauss Gestaltungsprozesse und andererseits führen die von ihm initiierten Prozesse selbst zu Formen mit einer inneren Logik. Das Buch macht beide anschaulich.   aStauss is the winner of the 2015 Stankowski Prize. The foundation's mission is to highlight the unity of art and design. Kilian Strauss uses an interdisciplinary approach in working in the areas of product, graphic, and interior design as well as interface design, signage, furniture design and teaching, and fully embodies this mission. Shaping Processes illustrates a wide selection of his projects over a period of nearly 20 years.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 4aCorperate Identity. 4aDesign. 4aGestaltung. 4aGrafik. 4aMedien. 4aMonographie. 7aDESIGN / Industrial.2bisacsh1 aStankowski Stiftung, , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2015z9783110438642oZDB-23-DKA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG0 cprintz978303560416040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978303560425240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783035604252423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783035604252.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2015  aZDB-23-DKAb2015